I"Ð<p>Setting up Home Assistant to run as a background service is simple; macOS will start Home Assistant after the system has booted, the user has logged in, and make sure itâ€™s always running.</p>
<p>To get Home Assistant installed as a background service, run:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">$ hass --script macos install

Home Assistant has been installed.         Open it here: http://localhost:8123
</code></pre>
<p>Home Assistant will log to <code>~/Library/Logs/homeassistant.log</code></p>
<p>Configuration is kept in <code>~/.homeassistant</code></p>
<p>To uninstall the service, run:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">$ hass --script macos uninstall

Home Assistant has been uninstalled.
</code></pre>
